[[div class="templateInfo"]]
+ What Is This?
----
A simple header design for the SCP Format, with a level-based Security Clearance modifier and lightweight "Disruption Class" bar.

**[[[*/anomaly-classification-system-guide#toc18|See this page for more information.]]]**
[[/div]]

[[div class="templateInfo"]]
+ How to Use
----
+++ Step 1. Copy me onto your page!
----
[[div class="code"]]
@@[[include :scp-wiki:component:flops-header@@
@@|item=@@
@@|containment=@@
@@|level=@@
@@|security=@@
@@|disruption=@@
@@|disruption-bg-color=@@
@@]]@@
[[/div]]
----
+++ Step 2. Read this short guide.
----
[[div_ class="help"]]
> Start of Include Block. ▷
> 
> Item Number. ▷
> 
> Object/Containment Class. ▷ **(Appears in Uppercase.)**
> 
> Clearance – Level Number. ▷
> 
> Clearance – Security Type Name. ▷ **(Appears in Uppercase.)**
> 
> Disruption Class Name. ▷ **(Appears in Uppercase.)**
> 
> Desired Bar Colour. ▷ **(Hex, RGB, & HSL Codes Allowed.)**
> 
> End of Include Block. ▷
> 

> [[include :scp-wiki:component:flops-header
> 
> |item={{0001–9999}}
> 
> |containment={{safe}}/{{euclid}}/{{keter}}/{{thaumiel}}/{{other}}
> 
> |level={{1–6}}
> 
> |security={{unrestricted}}/{{restricted}}/{{confidential}}/{{secret}}/{{top-secret}}/{{other}}
> 
> |disruption={{dark}}/{{vlam}}/{{keneq}}/{{ekhi}}/{{amida}}/{{other}}
> 
> |disruption-bg-color={{#00638a}}/{{#008a5c}}/{{#bd9d00}}/{{#bd5200}}/{{#8a0022}}/{{your choice}}
> 
> ]]
> 
[[/div]]
----
+++ Step 3. Fill in all fields after each = sign.
----
[[/div]]

[[div class="templateInfo"]]
+ Result
[[/div]]

[[include :scp-wiki:component:flops-header-source
|item=0000
|containment=thaumiel
|level=6
|security=the council
|disruption=undetermined
|disruption-bg-color=hsl(240, 15%, 37%)
]]

@@ @@
